00:10:52.730 --> 00:10:54.650
on Instagram in college is now your boss.

246
00:10:54.730 --> 00:10:57.440
I mean. it's also a never-meet-your-heroes
type of situation.

247
00:10:57.530 --> 00:10:59.530
But I'm proud.

248
00:10:59.610 --> 00:11:02.240
- I'm proud of you. too.
- Also. aren't you starting work tomorrow?

249
00:11:02.320 --> 00:11:04.700
Yes. and I need this job so bad.

250
00:11:04.780 --> 00:11:07.700
I looked at my student loan balance
and genuinely scared myself.

251
00:11:07.790 --> 00:11:09.410
- Hey. at your new job...
- Hm?

252
00:11:09.500 --> 00:11:11.040
I need you to try and make friends.

253
00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:13.210
Okay? I know that can be hard for you.

254
00:11:13.290 --> 00:11:15.670
What are you talking about? I'm lovely.

255
00:11:15.750 --> 00:11:17.590
I mean. unless somebody
breathes too loudly.

256
00:11:17.670 --> 00:11:19.220
and then obviously. I snap.

257
00:11:19.300 --> 00:11:20.800
You're not. You're anxious. angry.

258
00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:22.260
and obsessed with justice.

259
00:11:22.340 --> 00:11:23.930
And as much as I adore you. AJ.

260
00:11:24.010 --> 00:11:26.140
I cannot be your entire social ecosystem.

261
00:11:26.220 --> 00:11:27.890
Just put yourself out there.

262
00:11:27.970 --> 00:11:30.390
Be friendly. At least try.

263
00:11:31.310 --> 00:11:32.350
I can do that.

264
00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:42.070
Jocelyn. my lady.

265
00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:44.200
- How was the weekend?
- My Achilles flared.

266
00:11:44.280 --> 00:11:45.740
so I had to go to urgent care
to get it drained.

267
00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:47.660
Nurse was kinda hot. though.

268
00:11:47.740 --> 00:11:50.000
Self-care and a meet-cute. Damn. girl!

269
00:11:50.790 --> 00:11:52.460
Dileep. What's up. my man?

270
00:11:52.540 --> 00:11:55.790
Must we always fist bump?
A simple wave works.

271
00:11:55.880 --> 00:11:59.210
Absolutely not.
No. I need to feel your knuckles on mine.

272
00:11:59.840 --> 00:12:01.840
How was the weekend?

273
00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:05.300
Lovely. Sharmela and I
renewed our vows in Tennessee.

274
00:12:05.390 --> 00:12:07.600
Uh. Blackberry Farm in Walland.

275
00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:10.180
Voted most romantic place for couples
in the continental U.S.

276
00:12:10.270 --> 00:12:11.850
- Yes. Have you been?
- No.

277
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:14.810
No. I just hope to take someone there.

278
00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:15.980
Someday.

279
00:12:16.060 --> 00:12:17.900
God. I'm so lonely.

280
00:12:17.980 --> 00:12:21.610
Davis. when I met Sharmela at IIT.

281
00:12:21.690 --> 00:12:23.780
it was love at first sight.

282
00:12:23.860 --> 00:12:26.320
For me. Not for her.

283
00:12:26.410 --> 00:12:28.030
So. you know what I did?

284
00:12:28.120 --> 00:12:29.540
You wined. dined. and 69'ed her.

285
00:12:29.620 --> 00:12:31.250
I did not. and never say that again.

286
00:12:31.330 --> 00:12:34.790
I backed off. Became her friend.

287
00:12:34.870 --> 00:12:37.460
Eventually. Sharmela felt
the same way about me.

288
00:12:37.540 --> 00:12:39.880
I think you can learn from that. Davis.

289
00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:42.010
I mean. that goes against
my entire personality.

290
00:12:42.090 --> 00:12:43.970
But I'll try.

291
00:12:44.050 --> 00:12:45.430
Yeah. right. No chance in hell.

292
00:12:45.510 --> 00:12:47.100
Hey. give me a break. Jocelyn!

293
00:12:49.510 --> 00:12:52.680
Okay. so what famous people
are you dressing right now?

294
00:12:52.770 --> 00:12:55.520
Right now? Austin Blanchett.

295
00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:56.940
- Austin Blanchett?!
- Mm-hm!

296
00:12:57.020 --> 00:12:58.150
- Cate Blanchett's nephew?
- Yeah.

297
00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:01.030
- What is he like?
- No idea.

298
00:13:01.110 --> 00:13:04.820
Vanessa deals with him.
I just iron his socks.

299
00:13:04.900 --> 00:13:07.070
And that is important work. too.

300
00:13:07.160 --> 00:13:10.950
Okay. I am gonna head this way.
Get my run in.

301
00:13:11.040 --> 00:13:13.660
Oh. please. you're practicing
your commute to work. you nerd.

302
00:13:13.750 --> 00:13:15.540
Yeah. it's normal.

303
00:13:15.620 --> 00:13:17.920
No. it's not. but have fun.

304
00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:27.970
Next.

305
00:13:28.050 --> 00:13:29.510
Hey. yeah. double espresso.

306
00:13:31.310 --> 00:13:32.520
Uh. I was next.

307
00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:34.180
Uh. you were on your phone.
and the line moved.

308
00:13:34.270 --> 00:13:37.100
I was glancing at my phone
for two seconds.

309
00:13:37.190 --> 00:13:38.900
Yeah. well. I don't have all day
while you make your TikToks

310
00:13:38.980 --> 00:13:40.980
or whatever. alright?
Some of us have to work.

311
00:13:41.070 --> 00:13:43.070
- Are you kidding me?
- No. cellphones are a scourge

312
00:13:43.150 --> 00:13:44.320
and should be banned in public.

313
00:13:44.400 --> 00:13:47.530
- Keep the change.
- Hey. pal. I don't need an icy cold take

314
00:13:47.610 --> 00:13:51.530
on cellphones from some boomer dad
in orthopedic sneakers.

315
00:13:51.620 --> 00:13:55.040
Okay. I have plantar fasciitis.
and I was born in the '80s.

316
00:13:55.120 --> 00:13:58.120
You just told me we were born
in different centuries.

317
00:13:59.210 --> 00:14:02.750
Sir. I will pay you $100 to not serve
this woman over here.

318
00:14:02.840 --> 00:14:04.300
- What?
- Are you serious?

319
00:14:04.380 --> 00:14:06.630
You know. actually $500.

320
00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:09.510
Because this woman
wasted our valuable time.

321
00:14:09.590 --> 00:14:10.930
you deserve to be compensated...

322
00:14:11.010 --> 00:14:12.100
and she should learn a lesson.

323
00:14:12.180 --> 00:14:13.720
Yeah. I'll take it. Sorry. lady.

324
00:14:13.810 --> 00:14:16.020
Just 'cause you have $500 to throw around

325
00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:17.730
doesn't mean you get to be an asshole.

326
00:14:18.390 --> 00:14:20.610
That's exactly what it means. Cheers.

327
00:14:22.650 --> 00:14:23.860
Next.

328
00:14:23.940 --> 00:14:25.440
Mother...

329
00:14:38.790 --> 00:14:41.540
Wow. Paula Miller.
It is an honor to meet you.

330
00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:44.710
You are a feminist icon to women and men.

331
00:14:44.800 --> 00:14:47.970
You know. normally.
new PAs have three rounds of interviews

332
00:14:48.050 --> 00:14:49.510
- before they meet with me.
- Oh.

333
00:14:49.590 --> 00:14:51.720
Really. just to be clear.
I submitted my resume

334
00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:53.600
