like any other applicant.

335
00:14:53.680 --> 00:14:54.720
Right. right. right. right.

336
00:14:54.810 --> 00:14:57.980
But unlike all the other
hundreds of applicants.

337
00:14:58.060 --> 00:15:00.020
you're our CEO's son.

338
00:15:00.100 --> 00:15:01.190
Look. I get it.

339
00:15:01.270 --> 00:15:03.060
And there's a much-needed
conversation going on

340
00:15:03.150 --> 00:15:04.400
about nepotism in the workplace.

341
00:15:04.480 --> 00:15:05.820
But if we're gonna talk about that.

342
00:15:05.900 --> 00:15:08.990
we should also talk about whose land
we're on right now.

343
00:15:09.070 --> 00:15:12.490
It was the Lenape people
who were the first custodians and...

344
00:15:12.570 --> 00:15:15.410
Okay. stop. stop. stop.
You seem like a nice kid.

345
00:15:16.160 --> 00:15:17.540
But it's not gonna happen.

346
00:15:18.450 --> 00:15:19.790
You're not even gonna interview me?

347
00:15:19.870 --> 00:15:21.210
I've seen enough.

348
00:15:21.290 --> 00:15:22.420
You can go.

349
00:15:32.590 --> 00:15:34.180
I want you to put out a memo.

350
00:15:34.260 --> 00:15:36.220
and I cannot express
how important this is.

351
00:15:36.310 --> 00:15:39.180
No more microwaving lunch in the kitchen.

352
00:15:39.270 --> 00:15:41.480
The whole floor
smells like a fisherman's wharf.

353
00:15:41.560 --> 00:15:44.190
- Got it. No fish.
- Oh. my God. Wes Dryden.

354
00:15:44.270 --> 00:15:47.730
- Hello.
- I am such a big fan.

355
00:15:47.820 --> 00:15:51.820
Your show is literally the last bastion
of investigative journalism.

356
00:15:51.900 --> 00:15:53.450
Thank you.

357
00:15:53.530 --> 00:15:56.580
If truth disappears. so follows democracy.

358
00:15:57.950 --> 00:15:59.660
God. I hate the smell of fish.

359
00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:01.250
You want seafood? You have it at home.

360
00:16:01.330 --> 00:16:03.670
To be clear. I will continue to eat sushi.

361
00:16:03.750 --> 00:16:07.300
I actually just. uh.
interviewed for the new PA gig.

362
00:16:07.380 --> 00:16:09.130
Probably didn't get it.
but to have the opportunity

363
00:16:09.210 --> 00:16:10.550
to work for you.

364
00:16:10.630 --> 00:16:12.590
That's kind. but remember.

365
00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:15.680
it's a very competitive position.
You can always apply again.

366
00:16:15.760 --> 00:16:17.600
- Totally.
- Alright.

367
00:16:17.680 --> 00:16:19.180
Sorry. I didn't introduce myself.

368
00:16:19.930 --> 00:16:22.390
Josh. Teitelbaum.

369
00:16:24.020 --> 00:16:25.100
Teitelbaum.

370
00:16:25.940 --> 00:16:28.480
Well. I believe I know your father.

371
00:16:33.400 --> 00:16:35.320
Tomorrow is Austin's movie premiere.

372
00:16:35.410 --> 00:16:38.080
And I don't mean to sound scary.
but if anything goes wrong.

373
00:16:38.160 --> 00:16:39.330
I will fucking kill you.

374
00:16:39.410 --> 00:16:41.660
His fingers should never touch a button.

375
00:16:41.750 --> 00:16:42.830
Anticipate.

376
00:16:42.910 --> 00:16:44.330
Also. he might not be wearing underwear.

377
00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:45.920
so please do not gawk at his genitals.

378
00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:47.960
Got it. Don't look at his penis.

379
00:16:48.880 --> 00:16:51.630
Or his scrotum. Abby.

380
00:16:51.710 --> 00:16:54.180
Alright. so this is what he'll be wearing.

381
00:16:54.260 --> 00:16:56.760
Oh. wow.

382
00:16:57.600 --> 00:17:00.060
- Where's the shirt?
- There is no shirt.

383
00:17:00.140 --> 00:17:02.230
This is that new Danish designer. Blemish.

384
00:17:02.310 --> 00:17:04.520
Austin wears this.
we get the Blemish campaign.

385
00:17:04.600 --> 00:17:06.730
which pays way more
than an indie film premiere.

386
00:17:06.810 --> 00:17:08.480
So. why bring options?

387
00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:11.030
The illusion of choice.
This goes on the rack first.

388
00:17:11.110 --> 00:17:13.610
followed by a bunch of crap.
He'll beg to wear it.

389
00:17:14.360 --> 00:17:18.370
So. y-you want me to put together
a bunch of bad outfits?

390
00:17:18.450 --> 00:17:20.870
Welcome to the conversation. Yes.

391
00:17:26.500 --> 00:17:28.830
Can I show you my outfit
for my first day of work?

392
00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:30.130
Desperately. Yes.

393
00:17:31.250 --> 00:17:34.880
I think it's cool.
It's business. but the broach says fun.

394
00:17:34.970 --> 00:17:37.760
It says. "I manage a dialysis center."

395
00:17:37.840 --> 00:17:39.800
What? Oh. God!

396
00:17:39.890 --> 00:17:41.810
I'm spiraling. Everyone in finance

397
00:17:41.890 --> 00:17:44.180
dresses like a Vogue intern
who also has an MBA.

398
00:17:44.270 --> 00:17:45.430
Hey. Hey.

399
00:17:45.520 --> 00:17:46.980
Okay. when I met you freshman year.

400
00:17:47.060 --> 00:17:50.020
I thought. who is this angry little boy
in a Rajon Rondo jersey?

401
00:17:50.110 --> 00:17:51.650
- Rondo's the best.
- And then. I marched

402
00:17:51.730 --> 00:17:53.280
right over to the registrar
to get reassigned.

403
00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:55.780
- You did?
- And when they wouldn't let me.

404
00:17:55.860 --> 00:17:58.320
it was the best thing that ever happened.

405
00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:02.160
Because this little Boston townie is
a low-key genius with integrity.

406
00:18:02.240 --> 00:18:04.160
Everyone at your job will see that.

407
00:18:04.250 --> 00:18:06.660
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

408
00:18:07.370 --> 00:18:10.130
Now. let's get you something different.
This outfit is hurting our friendship.

409
00:18:10.210 --> 00:18:12.670
Oh. my God. I love you forever.

410
00:18:14.590 --> 00:18:16.300
What is that smell?

411
00:18:22.220 --> 00:18:25.220
It's my flat iron.
I was using it to iron my clothes.

412
00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:30.270
Mouthwash is flammable!

413
00:18:33.610 --> 00:18:36.030
You got the job? I'm so proud of you.

414
00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:38.860
- Yeah.
- Fucking Christiane Amanpour over here.

415
00:18:38.950 --> 00:18:41.950
No. it... it didn't happen
the way I expected.

416
00:18:42.030 --> 00:18:43.280
but you know what.
I'm gonna win 'em all over.

417
00:18:43.370 --> 00:18:44.830
Let's go get a drink and celebrate.

418
00:18:44.910 --> 00:18:47.540
I can't. I already took my melatonin.

419
00:18:47.620 --> 00:18:49.460
I could fall asleep at the bar
and get roofied.

420
00:18:49.540 --> 00:18:52.630
Kel. Thank God. someone fun.
Come get a drink with me.

421
00:18:52.710 --> 00:18:54.750
No. thanks. Didn't get the part.

422
00:18:54.840 --> 00:18:56.130
So I can't quit med school.

423
00:18:56.210 --> 00:18:58.630
I'll just be one of those sad-ass doctors

424
00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:00.930
who gets. like. too into the Oscars
every year.

425
00:19:01.010 --> 00:19:02.430
Oh. what the hell?

426
00:19:02.510 --> 00:19:05.220
Holy shit. you guys. it's a fire!
Come on. we gotta get out!

427
00:19:05.310 --> 00:19:06.680
I'm not gonna lose you like this.

428
00:19:06.770 --> 00:19:08.680
Grab the photo of us from Six Flags.

429
00:19:10.900 --> 00:19:12.310
Be careful.

430
00:19:12.400 --> 00:19:14.020
These garments are worth more
than your lives.

431
00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:18.070
- Okay. look. I have to tell you something.
- Ooh!

432
00:19:18.150 --> 00:19:19.650
My name's not on the lease.

433
00:19:19.740 --> 00:19:21.820
Ethan's is. That's why I keep his mail.

434
00:19:21.910 --> 00:19:23.780
I said he was a pilot and traveling.

435
00:19:23.870 --> 00:19:25.950
- You don't live here. you're visiting.
- Wait. what?

436
00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:28.120
Abby. How are you this evening?

437
00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:29.370
Oh. hey!

438
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:32.540
This is Antoine. my landlord. I'm great.

439
00:19:32.630 --> 00:19:35.000
I now have footage confirming
that you are good

440
00:19:35.090 --> 00:19:36.630
during this flame event.

441
00:19:36.710 --> 00:19:39.510
No legal liability. And you are?

442
00:19:39.590 --> 00:19:41.010
This is my friend.

443
00:19:41.090 --> 00:19:42.970
She's visiting from Sydney.

444
00:19:43.050 --> 00:19:45.010
Wow. all the way from Australia.

445
00:19:45.100 --> 00:19:46.390
- Mm-hmm.
- G'day. mate!

446
00:19:46.470 --> 00:19:48.520
Can you believe this bloody fire. mate?

447
00:19:48.600 --> 00:19:51.140
I didn't understand any of that.
but it was nice to meet you.

448
00:19:52.140 --> 00:19:53.310
What was that?

449
00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:54.980
Why didn't you just say I was from Boston?

450
00:19:55.060 --> 00:19:56.520
Because I'm not a professional liar. okay?

451
00:19:56.610 --> 00:19:58.320
It doesn't come naturally to me.

452
00:19:58.400 --> 00:20:00.400
Hey. can I speak to you privately?

453
00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:01.490
Uh...

454
00:20:02.820 --> 00:20:04.160
I'm so sorry about earlier.

455
00:20:04.240 --> 00:20:06.330
I just wanted to make you aware
that your roommate

456
00:20:06.410 --> 00:20:08.200
is committing rental fraud.

457
00:20:08.870 --> 00:20:12.750
- So?
- So. it's unethical. first of all.

458
00:20:12.830 --> 00:20:16.420
And second of all. me and my girlfriend...
she's a social worker. by the way...

459
00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:18.960
we're planning on moving in. Legally.

460
00:20:20.460 --> 00:20:23.260
Yeah. the creatine
was making my acne flare up.

461
00:20:23.340 --> 00:20:25.640
Oh. shit. Dude. it's Abby. four o'clock.

462
00:20:25.720 --> 00:20:27.560
Okay. now's your chance to go
and talk to her. she's by herself.

463
00:20:27.640 --> 00:20:30.390
No. no. she's not into me. and I already
took my contacts out. I... I can't.

464
00:20:30.470 --> 00:20:33.310
Hey. man. if you don't go
and talk to her. then I will.

465
00:20:33.390 --> 00:20:35.600
Then. she'll fall in love with me.
and it'll ruin our friendship.

466
00:20:35.690 --> 00:20:37.110
Okay. stop. stop. Fine.

467
00:20:37.190 --> 00:20:38.690
Okay. let's go.

468
00:20:38.770 --> 00:20:40.860
Yo. Abby. what's up?

469
00:20:40.940 --> 00:20:42.700
Crazy about this fire. huh?

470
00:20:42.780 --> 00:20:45.030
Oh. I hope Kel's medical textbooks
don't get burned up.

471
00:20:45.110 --> 00:20:47.160
Sorry. this is Kel.
He's in medical school.

472
00:20:47.240 --> 00:20:48.700
Yeah. I know.

473
00:20:48.780 --> 00:20:51.410
He told me when he hit on me
at that Halloween party in 4-C.

474
00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:53.080
What? I wasn't hitting on you.

475
00:20:53.160 --> 00:20:55.920
I... I just said you looked beautiful
in your Harley Quinn costume.

476
00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:57.590
and I asked to see your bedroom.

477
00:20:57.670 --> 00:21:00.500
Wow! Sparks. or...

478
00:21:00.590 --> 00:21:02.920
Well. I know when I'm a third wheel.

479
00:21:03.010 --> 00:21:04.880
Uh. good night. you crazy kids.

480
00:21:04.970 --> 00:21:06.590
I'm gonna see if I can sneak back in.

481
00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:11.430
- Ahem.
- So. you're in med school?

482
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.980
My parents would be so psyched
if I was gonna be a doctor.

483
00:21:14.060 --> 00:21:15.810
Yeah. I mean.
it's kinda the only reason I'm doing it.

484
00:21:16.560 --> 00:21:18.610
- What would you rather be doing?
- Honestly?

485
00:21:19.320 --> 00:21:21.070
I want to be an actor.

486
00:21:21.150 --> 00:21:23.780
When I was a kid. my parents put me
in the church nativity play.

487
00:21:23.860 --> 00:21:26.700
I was Joseph. and I... I killed it.

488
00:21:26.780 --> 00:21:28.240
I mean. they even gave me
some of Mary's lines.

489
00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:30.580
And I've been hooked ever since.

490
00:21:30.660 --> 00:21:33.410
And I feel like I found a piece of myself
I didn't know was missing.

491
00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:37.250
I'm sorry. I don't... I don't know why
I'm telling you all this.

492
00:21:37.330 --> 00:21:39.080
I mean. who knows if you can act.

493
00:21:39.170 --> 00:21:42.090
but I think you can make it.
You're pretty good-looking.

494
00:21:43.300 --> 00:21:44.420
I'm good-looking.

495
00:21:45.130 --> 00:21:47.840
- Oh. god.
- Damn. girl. our building is on fire.

496
00:21:47.930 --> 00:21:50.010
I'm just trying to stay alive.
I'm not trying to get hit on.

497
00:21:50.100 --> 00:21:51.430
I'm never making small talk
with you again.

498
00:21:51.510 --> 00:21:55.940
This is unbelievable! You are so
exhausting and self-important!

499
00:21:56.020 --> 00:21:58.730
Don't make us the villain
in your sob story.

500
00:21:58.810 --> 00:22:01.690
- There is a housing crisis!
- Then. move to New Jersey!

501
00:22:01.770 --> 00:22:04.280
- Ha!
- I'm sorry. is there a problem over here?

502
00:22:04.360 --> 00:22:06.860
Yeah. there's a problem.
You're both criminals.

503
00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:08.860
No wonder trust is eroding in our society.

504
00:22:08.950 --> 00:22:11.580
Hey. so don't saunter over here
making accusations.

505
00:22:11.660 --> 00:22:13.080
especially not in that cardigan.

506
00:22:13.160 --> 00:22:15.290
You look like a grandpa
in a Christmas commercial.

507
00:22:15.370 --> 00:22:17.670
Hey. don't talk to him like that.
Only we can say his cardigan sucks.

508
00:22:17.750 --> 00:22:19.330
This cardigan is cool!

509
00:22:19.420 --> 00:22:21.920
It gives me a quiet sophistication!

510
00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:24.420
Everyone. we've identified
the source of the fire.

511
00:22:24.510 --> 00:22:26.090
It was coming from 6-D.

512
00:22:26.170 --> 00:22:27.220
I knew it.

513
00:22:27.300 --> 00:22:28.590
It was a cheap flat iron.

514
00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:30.760
One of the ones you get
when you're traveling

515
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:32.850
and you forgot your nice one at home.

516
00:22:32.930 --> 00:22:34.770
- Her hair isn't even that good.
- Anyway.

517
00:22:34.850 --> 00:22:37.640
it's been contained.
You can all go back in.

518
00:22:41.110 --> 00:22:42.270
This isn't over.

519
00:22:43.570 --> 00:22:46.110
As a member of this building's community.

520
00:22:46.190 --> 00:22:47.650
I don't feel safe anymore.

521
00:22:47.740 --> 00:22:50.070
This could have been another
Triangle Shirtwaist Factory.

522
00:22:50.160 --> 00:22:52.410
That was the deadliest
industrial disaster in...

523
00:22:52.490 --> 00:22:54.830
Oh. I know
the Triangle Shirtwaist Factory.

524
00:22:54.910 --> 00:22:56.540
Yeah. Josh. Antoine was the dance captain

525
00:22:56.620 --> 00:22:58.410
for the musical adaptation on Broadway.

526
00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:00.210
It. too. went down in flames.

527
00:23:00.830 --> 00:23:02.630
Okay. well. I'm very sorry to hear that.

528
00:23:02.710 --> 00:23:05.210
But as our landlord.
I think you should know.

529
00:23:05.300 --> 00:23:09.300
the original leaseholder of 6-D
no longer lives there.

530
00:23:09.380 --> 00:23:11.720
The current tenants
are committing rental fraud.

531
00:23:11.800 --> 00:23:13.600
Those little bitches.

532
00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:16.970
That word is problematic.
but I don't disagree.

533
00:23:17.060 --> 00:23:19.480
The good news.
I have an amazing replacement.

534
00:23:19.560 --> 00:23:21.480
My girlfriend and me.

535
00:23:21.560 --> 00:23:23.360
We don't smoke. We don't own pets.

536
00:23:23.440 --> 00:23:24.690
- They don't have sex.
- We do.

537
00:23:24.770 --> 00:23:26.690
We just don't make a whole thing about it.

538
00:23:26.780 --> 00:23:29.240
And we can pay the security deposit
in cash.

539
00:23:29.320 --> 00:23:31.410
First month. last month.
and I get to store my snowboard

540
00:23:31.490 --> 00:23:33.070
- in the second bedroom.
- Deal.

541
00:23:33.160 --> 00:23:35.780
Always a pleasure doing business
with you gentlemen.

542
00:23:35.870 --> 00:23:38.080
And don't think I didn't see
that space heater.

543
00:23:39.290 --> 00:23:41.960
- My feet get cold.
- Get some socks.

544
00:23:43.920 --> 00:23:45.290
It's not a human.

545
00:23:46.250 --> 00:23:47.420
It's just a piece of meat.

546
00:23:48.630 --> 00:23:50.220
It's a piece of meat
with hopes and dreams.

547
00:23:50.300 --> 00:23:52.130
No. shh. it's not helping.

548
00:23:53.140 --> 00:23:56.060
You are a doctor. Pretend to be a doctor.

549
00:23:56.140 --> 00:23:57.680
Kel. we can all hear you.

550
00:23:58.680 --> 00:23:59.980
This is very awkward for us.

551
00:24:00.060 --> 00:24:01.270
Sorry.

552
00:24:04.690 --> 00:24:07.110
Fine work. You've come a long way. Kel.

553
00:24:07.190 --> 00:24:10.110
And that rush you're feeling.
that's the reason we do this.

554
00:24:10.190 --> 00:24:11.530
Yeah.

555
00:24:11.610 --> 00:24:13.360
What if I don't feel anything?

556
00:24:14.110 --> 00:24:15.780
- Excuse me?
- Yeah. like... like I just

557
00:24:15.870 --> 00:24:17.580
cut this guy open. and...

558
00:24:18.740 --> 00:24:19.870
I don't feel anything.

559
00:24:19.950 --> 00:24:22.830
And not in like a... like a Dexter.
"I'm a serial killer" kinda way.

560
00:24:22.920 --> 00:24:26.750
but you know. like a. "I just don't
find it fulfilling or even interesting."

561
00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:28.710
You know. like when you cut open
an Amazon box

562
00:24:28.800 --> 00:24:30.300
and you already know it's printer paper.

563
00:24:30.380 --> 00:24:31.880
Is everything okay?

564
00:24:31.970 --> 00:24:33.800
- Are you going to faint?
- Yeah. no. no. I...

565
00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:35.430
- I can't carry you out again.
- No. no. no.

566
00:24:35.510 --> 00:24:39.100
I think I thought that at some point.
if I got good enough.

567
00:24:39.180 --> 00:24:41.020
that it would click and I would love it.

568
00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:43.390
And that's just not happening.
That's not fair to you guys.

569
00:24:43.480 --> 00:24:46.940
or to you. Dr. Desai.
or to this uncircumcised cadaver.

570
00:24:47.020 --> 00:24:49.190
So. I think I'm just gonna go.

571
00:24:49.270 --> 00:24:50.650
Excuse me.

572
00:24:52.700 --> 00:24:54.360
Hm. that was weird.

573
00:24:55.280 --> 00:24:57.410
- You did what?!
- I quit medical school.

574
00:24:57.490 --> 00:24:59.370
Like. quit. quit?

575
00:24:59.450 --> 00:25:01.200
Yeah. I walked out of the cadaver lab.

576
00:25:01.290 --> 00:25:03.330
just got on the six.
and I guess somewhere along the line.

577
00:25:03.410 --> 00:25:04.830
I impulse bought this sweatshirt.

578
00:25:06.960 --> 00:25:08.960
What's with the big pause?
Be happy for me. this is a good thing.

579
00:25:09.040 --> 00:25:11.300
Is it? You don't have a job.

580
00:25:11.380 --> 00:25:12.720
You're not in school. You're basically a...

581
00:25:12.800 --> 00:25:15.760
A big fat loser. bro.
in a child-sized sweatshirt.

582
00:25:15.840 --> 00:25:17.970
That explains why
the neck hole is so small.

583
00:25:18.050 --> 00:25:20.850
But I'm not a loser.
I'm finally free to pursue my dreams.

584
00:25:20.930 --> 00:25:23.180
I'm just processing.
I've known you since you were 12.

585
00:25:23.270 --> 00:25:25.140
and you've never done anything
this impulsive.

586
00:25:25.230 --> 00:25:28.860
I also don't think you've blinked once
since you started talking.

587
00:25:28.940 --> 00:25:30.900
'Cause my eyes are open
to the truth of who I am.

588
00:25:30.980 --> 00:25:32.440
And your parents are cool with this?

589
00:25:33.280 --> 00:25:35.200
- I haven't told 'em yet.
- Are you kidding me?

590
00:25:35.280 --> 00:25:38.070
So. that's why you're in such a good mood.
You haven't been murdered by your mom yet.

591
00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:40.870
I can handle my mom.
but you two need to get on board.

592
00:25:40.950 --> 00:25:42.490
That's what being friends
is all about. right?

593
00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:44.330
We support each other
even when it doesn't make sense.

594
00:25:44.410 --> 00:25:46.540
Like when you dyed your hair
to look like Machine Gun Kelly.

595
00:25:46.620 --> 00:25:48.830
Oh. yes. I was thinking
of doing that again.

596
00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:51.130
- No.
- Kel. I'll admit. you've been miserable.

597
00:25:51.210 --> 00:25:54.380
and I miss seeing the light in your eyes.
so congrats.

598
00:25:54.470 --> 00:25:57.590
And you deserve to be happy
for the 18 hours before your mom

599
00:25:57.680 --> 00:25:59.430
- finds out and kills you.
- Thank you.

600
00:26:06.770 --> 00:26:08.270
Oh. my God.

601
00:26:08.350 --> 00:26:09.810
Is that good or bad?

602
00:26:09.900 --> 00:26:11.900
You look like such a finance bitch.

603
00:26:11.980 --> 00:26:14.440
Power suit. check.
No-makeup makeup. check.

604
00:26:14.530 --> 00:26:16.200
Coach Tabby bag. check.

605
00:26:16.280 --> 00:26:18.700
I would give you all my money
to lose in a Ponzi scheme.

606
00:26:18.780 --> 00:26:20.280
They're gonna love you.

607
00:26:20.950 --> 00:26:23.040
And I like that outfit you're styling.

608
00:26:23.120 --> 00:26:25.120
It's so... artsy?

609
00:26:25.200 --> 00:26:26.500
It's supposed to be bad.

610
00:26:26.580 --> 00:26:28.040
Oh. great. You killed it.

611
00:26:28.120 --> 00:26:30.210
Okay. wish me luck.

612
00:26:52.020 --> 00:26:53.610
Oh. my God.

613
00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:06.620
You got this. Pascarelli.

614
00:27:23.890 --> 00:27:26.060
Hi. Um. I'm AJ.

615
00:27:26.140 --> 00:27:27.770
New consumer and retail analyst.

616
00:27:27.850 --> 00:27:29.810
You must be our VP. Dileep?

617
00:27:29.890 --> 00:27:32.190
Yes. I emailed you a deal book
that needs formatting.

618
00:27:32.270 --> 00:27:34.110
And I would love to do that for you.
Do I have a desk?

619
00:27:34.730 --> 00:27:36.280
Great. Uh. do I have an email?

620
00:27:37.150 --> 00:27:39.610
You know what?
I will figure it out myself.

621
00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:45.240
No fucking way.

622
00:27:48.250 --> 00:27:50.290
You're our first-year?
The girl from the lobby.

623
00:27:50.370 --> 00:27:52.750
Wow. This... this is incredible.

624
00:27:52.830 --> 00:27:55.380
- What a warm welcome. Hi.
- Oh. man. you should be so psyched.

625
00:27:55.460 --> 00:27:57.750
Uh. first off. hi.

626
00:27:57.840 --> 00:27:59.590
I'm Davis Beau Bradley Barrett III.

627
00:27:59.670 --> 00:28:01.550
- Mm-hmm.
- And this is the best day of your life.

628
00:28:01.630 --> 00:28:03.760
You landed on the dream team.
My man Dileep and I.

629
00:28:03.840 --> 00:28:06.310
we crush deals.
And don't get me started on Jocelyn.

630
00:28:06.390 --> 00:28:08.180
She is a beast.

631
00:28:08.270 --> 00:28:10.770
Postponed foot surgery three times
so she didn't miss work.

632
00:28:10.850 --> 00:28:12.560
That's why she's got that badass cane.

633
00:28:12.640 --> 00:28:15.020
Ruptured Achilles.
It's excruciating. but it's worth it.

634
00:28:15.110 --> 00:28:17.400
I'm happy for you. How are the MDs?

635
00:28:17.480 --> 00:28:19.820
Oh. there's only one that matters.
Uh. Bill Gibson.

636
00:28:21.110 --> 00:28:22.950
The legend? Bill the Butcher?

637
00:28:23.030 --> 00:28:25.780
Youngest MD ever.
made 3 billion before 30?

638
00:28:25.870 --> 00:28:27.910
- He also dated a Hadid.
- Hey. that is just a rumor.

639
00:28:27.990 --> 00:28:29.910
- It's not a rumor.
- Where is he?

640
00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:32.790
Sorry. Oh.

641
00:28:32.870 --> 00:28:35.670
Bill doesn't work regular hours.
He makes his own rules.

642
00:28:35.750 --> 00:28:37.210
When he's here. you'll know.

643
00:28:37.290 --> 00:28:39.130
He lives in that office.

644
00:28:39.210 --> 00:28:40.880
Wow. Well. great.

645
00:28:40.960 --> 00:28:42.590
- Can't wait to be useful.
- Yeah.

646
00:28:46.220 --> 00:28:48.890
Hey. uh. I know we just met. but. um.

647
00:28:48.970 --> 00:28:50.970
I would really love to...

648
00:28:52.770 --> 00:28:56.270
be a. uh. resource
in your professional toolkit.

649
00:28:56.360 --> 00:28:58.690
Thank you. I appreciate it.

650
00:28:58.770 --> 00:28:59.780
Mm-hmm.

651
00:29:02.530 --> 00:29:04.450
Okey-dokey.

652
00:29:07.490 --> 00:29:09.490
Does anyone know what the password is?

653
00:29:09.580 --> 00:29:11.080
Yeah. I got it. I gotcha. yeah.

654
00:29:14.040 --> 00:29:16.000
Everyone! Attention. please.

655
00:29:16.080 --> 00:29:19.170
Attention! Meet Josh Teitelbaum.

656
00:29:20.090 --> 00:29:21.760
Yes. that Teitelbaum.

657
00:29:21.840 --> 00:29:23.470
Adding a touch of class to this place.

658
00:29:23.550 --> 00:29:25.050
He's our new production assistant.

659
00:29:25.130 --> 00:29:26.970
Isn't this glamorous?

660
00:29:27.050 --> 00:29:28.140
What?!

661
00:29:28.220 --> 00:29:29.720
I think he'll make a wonderful addition.

662
00:29:29.810 --> 00:29:32.270
Um. could we please
discuss this in private?

663
00:29:32.350 --> 00:29:33.850
No need. Paula. it's a done deal.

664
00:29:33.930 --> 00:29:36.980
Well. there were other
qualified candidates.

665
00:29:37.060 --> 00:29:38.360
like Elena.

666
00:29:38.440 --> 00:29:39.980
- Who's Elena?
- I'm Elena.

667
00:29:40.070 --> 00:29:41.480
I've been working here for a year.

668
00:29:41.570 --> 00:29:42.990
I drove you home from your colonoscopy.

669
00:29:43.070 --> 00:29:45.490
Oh. E-Elena.

670
00:29:46.320 --> 00:29:48.160
Yes. you're... you're great.

671
00:29:48.240 --> 00:29:51.080
You have to understand.
I was very high that day.

672
00:29:51.160 --> 00:29:54.330
Isn't it wonderful?
We can have Elena the intern

673
00:29:54.410 --> 00:29:56.500
and Josh both working here.

674
00:29:56.580 --> 00:29:59.040
Paula. get him a desk or something.

675
00:30:05.340 --> 00:30:07.340
- I brought cupcakes.
- Oh!

676
00:30:07.430 --> 00:30:09.590
Elena. you want to grab us
some plates and napkins?

677
00:30:13.060 --> 00:30:15.140
Not a good time.

678
00:30:17.810 --> 00:30:20.310
I know I wasn't your first choice.
but I am smart.

679
00:30:20.400 --> 00:30:22.610
I am hard-working. and I will prove to you

680
00:30:22.690 --> 00:30:24.070
that I was the right choice.

681
00:30:24.780 --> 00:30:26.450
Do you want to know how I got this job?

682
00:30:26.530 --> 00:30:27.740
Oh. yes!

683
00:30:27.820 --> 00:30:30.280
Please. Love an origin story.

684
00:30:30.370 --> 00:30:34.830
In the early '90s. things weren't great
for women in TV.

685
00:30:34.910 --> 00:30:36.710
I can't imagine.
You probably had to work

686
00:30:36.790 --> 00:30:38.540
twice as hard to rise up the ranks.

687
00:30:38.620 --> 00:30:41.750
I had to work ten times as hard.
and still got nowhere.

688
00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:44.550
So. I got creative. I married Wes.

689
00:30:45.920 --> 00:30:48.340
I'm sorry. you were married to Wes Dryden?

690
00:30:48.430 --> 00:30:52.600
But he's gay. and so are
you... 've never told me

691
00:30:52.680 --> 00:30:53.810
how you identify.

692
00:30:53.890 --> 00:30:55.430
Oh. we're both raging homos.

693
00:30:55.520 --> 00:30:57.680
But back then. Wes had to look

694
00:30:57.770 --> 00:30:59.980
like a family man for the anchor job.

695
00:31:00.060 --> 00:31:04.070
And I needed to seem
sexually palatable to one man

696
00:31:04.150 --> 00:31:05.980
to earn the respect of other men.

697
00:31:06.740 --> 00:31:08.400
That's the worst thing I've ever heard.

698
00:31:08.490 --> 00:31:11.160
Yeah. So. that's what I had to do.

699
00:31:11.240 --> 00:31:14.910
And to think. all you had to do

700
00:31:14.990 --> 00:31:16.620
was to say your last name.

701
00:31:17.250 --> 00:31:18.710
I am seeing the discrepancy.

702
00:31:18.790 --> 00:31:22.420
So. as long as I'm here.
you will never advance at the show.

703
00:31:22.500 --> 00:31:25.210
And I'm not going anywhere.
I've been on the Blue Zone diet

704
00:31:25.300 --> 00:31:27.130
since Clinton's first term.

705
00:31:27.210 --> 00:31:31.050
So. unless that cupcake
is made of algae. you can leave.

706
00:31:44.860 --> 00:31:46.440
Hi. Vanessa. Where are you?

707
00:31:46.530 --> 00:31:47.940
The fitting starts in ten minutes.

708
00:31:48.030 --> 00:31:50.200
I'm going to the hospital.

709
00:31:50.280 --> 00:31:52.450
What? What happened?

710
00:31:52.530 --> 00:31:55.950
I was in a taxi.
and there was stupid fucking gridlock.

711
00:31:56.030 --> 00:31:58.290
so I got out to walk.
and I got hit by a pedicab.

712
00:31:58.370 --> 00:32:00.960
A pedicab? How?
Those things go. like. two miles an hour.

713
00:32:01.040 --> 00:32:02.960
I may have been texting

714
00:32:03.040 --> 00:32:05.920
with Loewe's head of PR
and wasn't looking.

715
00:32:06.000 --> 00:32:09.460
Anyway. the point is.
you have to get Austin ready by yourself.

716
00:32:10.170 --> 00:32:11.590
Me? Alone?

717
00:32:11.680 --> 00:32:13.430
Oh. fuck my life. Yes.

718
00:32:13.510 --> 00:32:15.100
That's what "by yourself" means.

719
00:32:16.010 --> 00:32:17.720
God. now I'm panicking.

720
00:32:17.810 --> 00:32:20.600
Can you sedate me. sir?
Like in the movies?

721
00:32:20.680 --> 00:32:23.480
Vanessa. don't worry about it. I got it.

722
00:32:24.980 --> 00:32:27.110
Okay.

723
00:32:29.360 --> 00:32:32.110
Hi! Does anyone here
have any upper-body strength?

724
00:32:35.320 --> 00:32:38.870
Welcome to our first-year analyst
speaker series.

725
00:32:40.790 --> 00:32:45.170
We're thrilled to be talking with someone
who is very hard to pin down.

726
00:32:45.250 --> 00:32:47.670
Managing Director Bill Gibson.

727
00:32:50.800 --> 00:32:52.630
Oh. fuck me.

728
00:32:52.720 --> 00:32:54.590
So much is said

729
00:32:54.680 --> 00:32:58.050
about the intense lifestyle
of investment bankers.

730
00:32:58.140 --> 00:33:00.720
But at Fisher Stassen. we're working hard

731
00:33:00.810 --> 00:33:02.430
to reject that old trope.

732
00:33:02.520 --> 00:33:05.520
So. let's start with work-life balance.

733
00:33:05.600 --> 00:33:07.150
What's that quote?

734
00:33:07.230 --> 00:33:09.110
"No one on their deathbed

735
00:33:09.190 --> 00:33:11.940
ever said they wished they spent
more time in the office"?

736
00:33:12.030 --> 00:33:13.320
Yes. exactly.

737
00:33:13.400 --> 00:33:14.860
Total bullshit.

738
00:33:15.530 --> 00:33:18.330
Look. I'm from Bumfuck. Oklahoma. right?

739
00:33:18.410 --> 00:33:20.160
I was nobody until I got here.

740
00:33:20.240 --> 00:33:22.120
- You mean you found community.
- No.

741
00:33:22.200 --> 00:33:24.580
Fuck community. I found power.

742
00:33:24.660 --> 00:33:26.920
Look. you ever close
a billion-dollar merger?

743
00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:29.380
It's better than
the best night of sex you ever had.

744
00:33:29.460 --> 00:33:32.090
He's being metaphorical.

745
00:33:32.170 --> 00:33:33.340
No. I'm not.

746
00:33:33.420 --> 00:33:35.130
And it's not about the expense account

747
00:33:35.220 --> 00:33:36.840
or the drugs.
although those are great. too.

748
00:33:36.930 --> 00:33:38.390
It's about the leverage.

749
00:33:39.050 --> 00:33:40.220
That's real power.

750
00:33:40.310 --> 00:33:41.640
And about work-life balance.

751
00:33:41.720 --> 00:33:44.600
if this job were easy.
everyone would do it.

752
00:33:44.980 --> 00:33:47.270
Do you have anything inspirational

753
00:33:47.350 --> 00:33:50.150
- you could impart to our young people?
- Yeah.

754
00:33:51.690 --> 00:33:55.070
You're no longer young people.
You're just people.

755
00:33:55.150 --> 00:33:58.240
And people are either
productive or dead weight.

756
00:33:58.320 --> 00:34:01.830
So. if you want to take off on a Friday
to go to a music festival.

757
00:34:01.910 --> 00:34:03.790
or if you wanna whine because your boss

758
00:34:03.870 --> 00:34:06.410
won't let you grow a mustache.
if you're not willing

759
00:34:06.500 --> 00:34:09.420
to sacrifice everything for this job...

760
00:34:11.090 --> 00:34:12.750
the exit is right there.

761
00:34:13.920 --> 00:34:15.010
Uh. thank you. Bill.

762
00:34:15.090 --> 00:34:18.430
That was such a colorful.
unfiltered perspective.

763
00:34:18.510 --> 00:34:22.100
But remember.
that does not reflect company values.

764
00:34:22.180 --> 00:34:23.680
Please don't post this.

765
00:34:25.810 --> 00:34:27.560
Thank you so much
for meeting me. Naya.

766
00:34:27.640 --> 00:34:29.520
- How's work?
- Really good.

767
00:34:29.600 --> 00:34:31.610
It's a great time
to be in plastic surgery.

768
00:34:31.690 --> 00:34:34.070
Literally everyone hates how they look.
even hot people.

769
00:34:34.150 --> 00:34:36.240
- Huh!
- What's up?

770
00:34:37.150 --> 00:34:38.450
I'm dropping out of medical school.

771
00:34:38.530 --> 00:34:39.740
You're joking.

772
00:34:39.820 --> 00:34:42.450
Is this because you fainted
in the cadaver lab?

773
00:34:42.530 --> 00:34:44.700
- You know about that?
- Yes. everyone's talking about it.

774
00:34:44.790 --> 00:34:46.660
It's all over the Columbia Reddit.

775
00:34:46.750 --> 00:34:49.750
Kel. everyone hates med school
and thinks about dropping out.

776
00:34:49.830 --> 00:34:51.290
- You'll get over it.
- No. I won't.

777
00:34:51.380 --> 00:34:54.210
I'm miserable.
I don't even want to be a doctor.

778
00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:56.420
I just really need you on my side
when I tell Mom.

779
00:34:56.510 --> 00:34:59.760
I just need some time to figure out
what to say next time I see her.

780
00:34:59.840 --> 00:35:02.600
- Oh. my God. you're going to kill me.
- What? Why?

781
00:35:02.680 --> 00:35:04.350
- Mom's here.
- What?

782
00:35:04.430 --> 00:35:06.850
Well. she called me.
and I told her we were having lunch.

783
00:35:06.930 --> 00:35:08.350
so she asked if she could stop by.

784
00:35:08.440 --> 00:35:10.020
- Naya!
- I didn't know.

785
00:35:10.100 --> 00:35:12.860
- There are my babies!
- Mom.

786
00:35:12.940 --> 00:35:14.190
Mwah. Mwah.

787
00:35:14.270 --> 00:35:16.650
I didn't know you'd be here.
I... I love it.

788
00:35:16.740 --> 00:35:19.490
It's so hard to get both of you together.

789
00:35:19.570 --> 00:35:23.410
You're in surgery.
You're fainting in the cadaver lab.

790
00:35:23.490 --> 00:35:26.120
- Wow. so everyone knows.
- But what does it matter?

791
00:35:26.200 --> 00:35:27.910
You're becoming a doctor.

792
00:35:30.250 --> 00:35:31.670
Mom. I'm... I'm glad that you're here.

793
00:35:31.750 --> 00:35:33.630
I didn't think
I'd be telling you this now.

794
00:35:33.710 --> 00:35:35.130
- but I don't... I don't think I'm...
- In a second. Kel.

795
00:35:35.210 --> 00:35:37.170
I want to take our Christmas card photos.

796
00:35:37.260 --> 00:35:38.630
Christmas card photos?

797
00:35:38.720 --> 00:35:42.260
Yes. Both of you in your doctor coats.

798
00:35:42.340 --> 00:35:45.640
It's a festive way to let
our friends and family know

799
00:35:45.720 --> 00:35:48.220
my children
are more successful than theirs.

800
00:35:48.310 --> 00:35:50.020
That is what the holidays are all about.

801
00:35:50.100 --> 00:35:53.060
Now. Kel. what did you want to tell me?

802
00:35:54.900 --> 00:35:56.730
That this card rocks. Let's take this pic.

803
00:35:56.820 --> 00:35:58.650
Alright. now.

804
00:35:58.740 --> 00:36:00.360
Wait for these people to move.

805
00:36:00.450 --> 00:36:02.780
Let's do back-to-back. Bigger smiles.

806
00:36:02.860 --> 00:36:04.570
You love being a doctor!

807
00:36:04.660 --> 00:36:05.830
Yes.

808
00:36:11.080 --> 00:36:12.670
I've had a horrible day.

809
00:36:12.750 --> 00:36:15.250
My 60-year-old boss
told me she'll outlive me.

810
00:36:15.340 --> 00:36:16.800
and I think I believe her.

811
00:36:16.880 --> 00:36:18.800
I'm sorry to hear that.

812
00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:20.630
I got you Thai from Fish Cheeks.

813
00:36:21.300 --> 00:36:23.130
My favorite.

814
00:36:23.220 --> 00:36:25.930
You always know
how to make me feel better.

815
00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:31.100
What's up?
Wait. why do you have your suitcase?

816
00:36:31.180 --> 00:36:34.520
The food is actually a goodbye gift.
I'm leaving.

817
00:36:36.020 --> 00:36:38.360
- What?
- Josh. I'm not in love with you anymore.

818
00:36:38.440 --> 00:36:41.490
Are you kidding me?
I... I'm getting our neighbors evicted

819
00:36:41.570 --> 00:36:43.320
so we can move in together.

820
00:36:43.410 --> 00:36:46.120
Well. about that. It's the craziest thing.

821
00:36:46.200 --> 00:36:49.870
I was looking at an apartment.
and just randomly.

822
00:36:49.950 --> 00:36:52.160
the guy who was showing me the listing.

823
00:36:52.250 --> 00:36:54.080
we just hit it off.

824
00:36:54.170 --> 00:36:56.540
You're leaving me for a real estate agent?

825
00:36:56.630 --> 00:36:58.550
Well. he's not just a real estate agent.

826
00:36:58.630 --> 00:37:00.760
Josh. he's a Property Brother.

827
00:37:00.840 --> 00:37:03.590
I mean. not the one with Zooey Deschanel
or that guy's twin.

828
00:37:03.680 --> 00:37:05.090
but their younger brother.

829
00:37:05.180 --> 00:37:08.220
You're leaving me
for a nonessential Property Brother?

830
00:37:08.300 --> 00:37:10.520
Uh. do not talk about Eric like that.

831
00:37:10.600 --> 00:37:12.520
Eric? The fuck?

832
00:37:12.600 --> 00:37:14.270
It was electric when we met.

833
00:37:14.350 --> 00:37:17.400
and it made me realize what is missing
in our relationship.

834
00:37:17.480 --> 00:37:19.770
- What are we missing?
- Well. he's fun!

835
00:37:19.860 --> 00:37:22.940
And he isn't embarrassed that he's rich.

836
00:37:23.030 --> 00:37:26.490
I mean. we will go to a restaurant
even if the Sultan of Brunei owns it.

837
00:37:26.570 --> 00:37:28.780
or wear leather without it
being a whole thing.

838
00:37:28.870 --> 00:37:31.080
Oh. I'm sorry. I'm not complicit
in cow genocide.

839
00:37:31.160 --> 00:37:35.710
You know. the irony is.
if you met him. you would love him.

840
00:37:35.790 --> 00:37:38.170
I don't want to hear about your stupid
fucking realtor boyfriend. Vivian.

841
00:37:38.250 --> 00:37:40.420
Take your Thai food and go.

842
00:37:44.970 --> 00:37:47.470
And for what it's worth.
you can keep my Brita.

843
00:37:47.550 --> 00:37:49.890
Eric lets me drink single-use plastics.

844
00:37:50.810 --> 00:37:52.770
Congratulations. you're dating a monster.

845
00:37:56.390 --> 00:37:58.400
Yeah. I'm not doing a spray tan.

846
00:37:58.480 --> 00:38:01.230
It's the Independent Spirit Awards.
not the VMAs.

847
00:38:01.320 --> 00:38:03.400
I mean. would Paul Mescal do a spray tan?

848
00:38:04.900 --> 00:38:06.570
Oh. it's his guy?

849
00:38:06.650 --> 00:38:08.110
Yeah. alright. let's do it.

850
00:38:08.200 --> 00:38:09.660
Okay. gotta go.

851
00:38:09.740 --> 00:38:11.870
- Yeah. can we just make this fast?
- Sure.

852
00:38:11.950 --> 00:38:13.290
Um. I'm Abby.

853
00:38:14.700 --> 00:38:17.750
I'm filling in for Vanessa.
who is indisposed.

854
00:38:17.830 --> 00:38:18.920
Who's Vanessa?

855
00:38:19.750 --> 00:38:23.000
- She's your stylist.
- Oh. the tiny. grouchy woman?

856
00:38:23.090 --> 00:38:24.090
- Mm-hmm.
- Cool.

857
00:38:24.170 --> 00:38:25.760
What are we wearing?

858
00:38:26.470 --> 00:38:27.470
Uh...

859
00:38:30.220 --> 00:38:31.930
Here we go.

860
00:38:32.010 --> 00:38:33.350
Righto.

861
00:38:37.100 --> 00:38:40.520
Let me know if you need
any help getting into it.

862
00:38:42.820 --> 00:38:44.610
Vanessa loves this for you.

863
00:38:44.690 --> 00:38:46.690
It's. uh. this designer Blemish.

864
00:38:46.780 --> 00:38:49.780
They're European. Very avant-garde.

865
00:38:51.030 --> 00:38:52.120
Oh.

866
00:38:52.780 --> 00:38:56.080
I love it.
It's. uh. s-such a choice.

867
00:38:56.160 --> 00:38:57.540
Oh. yeah?

868
00:38:57.620 --> 00:39:00.330
I mean. I think we can both agree
this is horrible.

869
00:39:00.420 --> 00:39:02.090
But it doesn't matter.

870
00:39:02.170 --> 00:39:04.710
Fashion is not important.

871
00:39:05.630 --> 00:39:08.130
- What?
- Fashion's not not important

872
00:39:08.220 --> 00:39:09.760
just because you don't understand it.

873
00:39:09.840 --> 00:39:12.890
Oh. are you seriously trying to tell me
this is a normal. cool way to dress?

874
00:39:12.970 --> 00:39:14.600
I look like a time-traveling stripper.

875
00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:17.770
Okay. I agree that maybe
it's a little over the top.

876
00:39:17.850 --> 00:39:20.520
I didn't get into acting
to make a fashion statement.

877
00:39:20.600 --> 00:39:22.230
I mean. it's about the work.

878
00:39:22.310 --> 00:39:23.770
not what I wear.

879
00:39:23.860 --> 00:39:26.150
Are you gonna keep making
these little sounds?

880
00:39:26.230 --> 00:39:29.070
I just... I'm sorry.
If it is just about the work.

881
00:39:29.150 --> 00:39:30.860
then why do red carpets exist?

882
00:39:30.950 --> 00:39:32.910
Because if the audience
is into the fashion.

883
00:39:32.990 --> 00:39:34.660
they're way more likely to see your movie.

884
00:39:34.740 --> 00:39:36.830
Fair enough.
But I still don't like the suit.

885
00:39:36.910 --> 00:39:38.540
So unless you have something else
that I can wear.

886
00:39:38.620 --> 00:39:42.500
Miss Fashion Justice Warrior.
I'm gonna rock my t-shirt and jeans.

887
00:39:42.580 --> 00:39:43.750
Okay. wait. Wait.

888
00:39:43.840 --> 00:39:46.800
I. I... I might have something for you.

889
00:39:46.880 --> 00:39:51.340
Most of this rack is garbage.
but I snuck something good in.

890
00:39:51.430 --> 00:39:53.930
Are you sure about that color?
I'm gonna look like a pomegranate.

891
00:39:54.010 --> 00:39:55.260
It's Dolce and Gabbana.

892
00:39:56.350 --> 00:39:59.230
Colin Farrell's worn them.

893
00:40:00.140 --> 00:40:01.390
- Colin Farrell?
- Mm-hmm.

894
00:40:02.230 --> 00:40:04.860
Really? Alright.
Well. I'll try.

895
00:40:21.500 --> 00:40:22.710
Not tonight. rapist!

896
00:40:24.540 --> 00:40:26.090
What the hell? Davis?

897
00:40:26.170 --> 00:40:27.300
Why did you do that?

898
00:40:27.380 --> 00:40:29.010
Why are you following me?

899
00:40:29.090 --> 00:40:30.380
I'm not. I'm walking home!

900
00:40:30.470 --> 00:40:32.630
- Home? Where?
- Right here.

901
00:40:32.720 --> 00:40:34.840
- I'm 6-C.
- I'm 6-D.

902
00:40:34.930 --> 00:40:36.930
Oh. my God. do you live with Josh

903
00:40:37.010 --> 00:40:39.270
and that hot guy
who's obsessed with my roommate?

904
00:40:39.350 --> 00:40:41.480
I think people consider me
the hot one. but yes.

905
00:40:41.560 --> 00:40:43.770
- Oh. my God. my eyes!
- Oh. I'm so sorry.

906
00:40:43.850 --> 00:40:46.520
- Davis. is there anything I can do?
- It's fine. it's fine. it's fine.

907
00:40:46.610 --> 00:40:48.860
- I'm fine.
- Okay. Sorry again.

908
00:40:48.940 --> 00:40:50.690
Stressful day.

909
00:40:50.780 --> 00:40:54.660
May I ask. is Bill.
like. forgiving and chill?

910
00:40:54.740 --> 00:40:56.070
No. no. not at all.

911
00:40:56.160 --> 00:40:58.660
There's a reason
your analyst job was open.

912
00:40:58.740 --> 00:41:00.200
He fired the previous girl
'cause he didn't like

913
00:41:00.290 --> 00:41:02.210
how she spelled her name. Erika with a K.

914
00:41:02.290 --> 00:41:04.500
It's not even that weird
of a way to spell Erika.

915
00:41:05.170 --> 00:41:09.420
And what if someone at work
called him. like. an asshole?

916
00:41:09.500 --> 00:41:11.420
He'd kill them and fire them.

917
00:41:11.510 --> 00:41:13.220
- in that order.
- Oh. God.

918
00:41:13.300 --> 00:41:16.140
And all I wanted was for one person
at work to like me.

919
00:41:18.300 --> 00:41:19.430
I like you.

920
00:41:20.930 --> 00:41:21.930
Thank you.

921
00:41:22.930 --> 00:41:26.770
I mean. it means slightly less
because you seem to like everyone.

922
00:41:27.610 --> 00:41:30.270
Guilty. But I usually don't feel that way

923
00:41:30.360 --> 00:41:32.110
about people who just pepper-sprayed me.

924
00:41:32.190 --> 00:41:34.570
So. you're good.

925
00:41:36.450 --> 00:41:37.660
Anyways. I'm gonna go in

926
00:41:37.740 --> 00:41:39.450
and rinse my eyes
just to make sure I'm not blind.

927
00:41:39.530 --> 00:41:42.080
Of course. So sorry again.

928
00:41:42.160 --> 00:41:43.370
Uh. good luck.

929
00:41:49.920 --> 00:41:52.210
Oh. my God. You look so good.

930
00:41:52.300 --> 00:41:54.010
- Really?
- Yeah.

931
00:41:54.090 --> 00:41:55.970
- It's pretty red.
- It suits you.

932
00:41:56.050 --> 00:41:58.050
People are gonna lose it
when they see you play that dying guy

933
00:41:58.140 --> 00:41:59.510
that ends up with Ana de Armas.

934
00:41:59.600 --> 00:42:01.010
You googled my movie.

935
00:42:01.100 --> 00:42:02.430
Yeah. of course I did.

936
00:42:02.520 --> 00:42:04.270
The work is important. too.

937
00:42:04.350 --> 00:42:06.230
Almost as important as the fashion.

938
00:42:06.980 --> 00:42:08.900
Okay. well. take it off.
I need to steam it.

939
00:42:14.320 --> 00:42:15.950
Were you just checking me out?

940
00:42:16.030 --> 00:42:17.320
What? No!

941
00:42:17.410 --> 00:42:19.240
Absolutely not. That is so unprofessional.

942
00:42:19.320 --> 00:42:20.830
I would never.

943
00:42:21.620 --> 00:42:22.790
That's too bad.

944
00:42:37.760 --> 00:42:40.050
Ruth Bader Twinsburg.

945
00:42:41.640 --> 00:42:43.640
That was such a fucking good costume.

946
00:42:44.640 --> 00:42:46.100
Um. take out for AJ?

947
00:42:46.180 --> 00:42:49.980
I know you are sad.
but it is time to pay.

948
00:42:52.230 --> 00:42:55.150
Shit. I left my wallet upstairs.

949
00:42:55.230 --> 00:42:57.530
- Can I Venmo you?
- Venmo?

950
00:42:57.610 --> 00:42:58.860
This is a restaurant.

951
00:42:58.950 --> 00:43:01.160
We are not roommates
with a shared utility bill.

952
00:43:01.240 --> 00:43:03.370
- I'll just run up and grab it.
- I cannot let you leave.

953
00:43:03.450 --> 00:43:07.250
Hey. man. I just had my heart shattered
an hour ago.

954
00:43:07.330 --> 00:43:08.660
I don't know
if that's ever happened to you.

955
00:43:08.750 --> 00:43:10.420
- No. I have never been dumped.
- Okay.

956
00:43:10.500 --> 00:43:13.090
Well. can you give me a break
and let me run upstairs and get the money?

957
00:43:13.170 --> 00:43:15.380
- I can pay. I have cash.
- No!

958
00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:16.880
- Great.
- Absolutely not.

959
00:43:16.960 --> 00:43:18.720
- She is a good friend.
- Oh. we are not.

960
00:43:20.640 --> 00:43:22.680
You really didn't need to do that.

961
00:43:22.760 --> 00:43:23.970
You know. I had it covered.

962
00:43:24.060 --> 00:43:26.470
You shouldn't rip off small businesses.
That's not okay.

963
00:43:26.560 --> 00:43:28.100
I wasn't doing that.
I love small business.

964
00:43:28.180 --> 00:43:29.440
You could just say thank you.

965
00:43:30.690 --> 00:43:31.690
Thank you.

966
00:43:31.770 --> 00:43:34.270
Great. Gonna get my food.

967
00:43:35.230 --> 00:43:36.400
Wait. hold on.

968
00:43:37.360 --> 00:43:38.650
Have we met before?

969
00:43:39.610 --> 00:43:41.360
Well. um. yeah.

970
00:43:41.450 --> 00:43:42.950
- I live across the hall.
- No. no. no.

971
00:43:43.030 --> 00:43:44.580
Like. before that.

972
00:43:44.660 --> 00:43:46.580
You seem so familiar.

973
00:43:47.580 --> 00:43:51.290
Well. maybe your conscience
wants you to be nicer to me.

974
00:43:52.380 --> 00:43:54.250
Fair.

975
00:43:54.340 --> 00:43:55.840
Thanks again.

976
00:43:55.920 --> 00:43:58.460
- I'll pay you back.
- Sweet.

977
00:44:05.640 --> 00:44:09.480
Hey. Antoine. Forget what we said
about the girls in 6D. My bad.

978
00:44:12.190 --> 00:44:15.190
Hey. can you talk tomorrow?
I might need a job.

979
00:44:18.070 --> 00:44:19.820
Oh. my God. what happened to you?

980
00:44:20.990 --> 00:44:22.820
I was just pepper-sprayed.

981
00:44:22.910 --> 00:44:24.200
Why are you smiling?

982
00:44:25.240 --> 00:44:28.160
